<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Cochran, Andrew William. Eight letters to Roderick Mackenzie, 1823-1837. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0004</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:right;">Quebec 20<sup>th</sup> March</p>
<p style="text-align:right;"><span class="fw" style="text-decoration:underline;">1823</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">My Dear Sir</p>
<p class="positiveIndent">I have to thank you for your letter of the 15<sup>th</sup> and for mentioning me to your friend D<sup>r</sup> Fraser, whose interest I shall immediately attend to; I am only Sorry that <span class="DelHand-author">they did</span> his instructions did not reach me sooner than yesterday<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  It is too late, by some days, to commence proceedings for the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">first</span> day of next term, in consequence of which no judgments can be obtained (if the opposite party chuses to <span class="DelHand-author">oppo</span> put it off,) until next term.  I shall however take the proper steps in the business without delay.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">I write from the Council Chamber<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The appropriation Bills for the <span class="AddHand-author">unpaid</span> arrears of <span style="text-decoration:underline;">1822</span> and for the expences of <span style="text-decoration:underline;">1823</span> passed a day or two ago in Council; with a sort of protest<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The La Salle Bill has been amended today in such a way that</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">it</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The Hon<sup>ble</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">R Mackenzie Esq</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[1]</span></p>

</div>
